---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Use Cases — JamJet"
  description="Real production use cases for JamJet: investment due diligence, customer support, code review pipelines, research automation, and more."
  canonical="https://jamjet.dev/usecases"
>

<!-- ── Hero ── -->
<section class="uc-hero">
  <span class="section-label">Use Cases</span>
  <h1>What you can build<br/>with JamJet</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:1.05rem;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto">
    Real production patterns — from multi-agent A2A pipelines to durable human-in-the-loop
    workflows. Each use case links to working code.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- ── Featured Case Study ── -->
<section style="background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 64px 24px;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="case-hero">

      <div class="case-eyebrow">Featured case study</div>

      <h2 class="case-title">Investment Due Diligence<br/>with Specialized Agents</h2>

      <p class="case-lead">
        A single company name triggers a parallel network of three specialized AI agents —
        each an independent HTTP service speaking the A2A protocol — that collaborates to
        produce a complete investment due diligence report.
      </p>

      <div class="metrics-row">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">1.35x</div>
          <div class="metric-label">parallel speedup</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">3</div>
          <div class="metric-label">agents, zero shared memory</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">&lt;5ms</div>
          <div class="metric-label">RAG retrieval per query</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">~6s</div>
          <div class="metric-label">wall-clock, full report</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="subsection-title">Architecture</h3>

      <div class="arch-block">┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  VC Analyst: <span style="color:var(--accent)">python run.py Anthropic</span>                          │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
                           ▼
           ┌───────────────────────────────┐
           │       Orchestrator            │
           │   (pure HTTP — no imports     │
           │    from agent modules)        │
           └──────┬─────────────┬──────────┘
                  │             │  Phase 2: submit tasks in parallel
    ┌─────────────▼─┐       ┌───▼─────────────┐
    │ Financial Agent│       │  Market Agent   │
    │    :7701       │       │     :7702       │
    │                │       │                 │
    │  RAG pipeline: │       │  RAG pipeline:  │
    │  financials.md │       │  markets.md     │
    │  → chunk →     │       │  → chunk →      │
    │  score →       │       │  score →        │
    │  retrieve →    │       │  retrieve →     │
    │  LLM           │       │  LLM            │
    └────────┬───────┘       └────────┬────────┘
             │                        │
             └──────────┬─────────────┘
                        │  Phase 4: combine + send to Risk Agent
                        ▼
           ┌────────────────────────────┐
           │       Risk Agent  :7703    │
           │                            │
           │  6-dimension risk rubric   │
           │  + LLM synthesis           │
           │  → scorecard + rating      │
           └─────────────┬──────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
          Full Due Diligence Report</div>

      <div class="case-body">
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why A2A — not a single agent</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Financial and market analysis are <strong>independent</strong> — parallel A2A cuts wall-clock time by 26%</li>
            <li>Each agent optimizes its own <strong>system prompt and temperature</strong> for its domain</li>
            <li>Swapping the Market Agent for a <strong>PitchBook integration</strong> is one URL change</li>
            <li>Each agent is a <strong>separate HTTP service</strong> — independently scalable</li>
            <li>Third-party agents can <strong>plug in via A2A</strong> — no SDK sharing needed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why RAG — not live web search</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Web-scraped financial figures are <strong>inconsistent across sources</strong></li>
            <li><strong>LLMs hallucinate specific numbers</strong> without grounding</li>
            <li>RAG retrieval is <strong>&lt;5ms</strong> — web search adds 2–5s per query</li>
            <li>Production data comes from <strong>signed data agreements</strong></li>
            <li>Swap to <strong>vector embeddings</strong> by replacing one function</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="a2a-endpoints">
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:16px">A2A protocol endpoints</h3>
        <div class="endpoint-grid">
          <div class="endpoint-card">
            <div class="endpoint-path">GET /.well-known/agent.json</div>
            <p>Agent Card — name, description, capabilities. The orchestrator fetches all three at startup.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint-card">
            <div class="endpoint-path">POST /a2a/tasks</div>
            <p>Submit a task with a skill_id and input. Returns a task_id immediately.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint-card">
            <div class="endpoint-path">GET /a2a/tasks/{'{id}'}</div>
            <p>Poll for result. Status: pending, running, complete.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timing-comparison">
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:16px">Sequential vs parallel</h3>
        <div class="timing-grid">
          <div class="timing-card timing-slow">
            <div class="timing-label">Sequential</div>
            <div class="timing-body">
              Financial: 1,842ms<br/>
              Market: 2,104ms<br/>
              Risk: 3,211ms<br/>
              <span class="timing-total" style="color:var(--error)">Total: ~7,157ms</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timing-card timing-fast">
            <div class="timing-label" style="color:var(--success)">Parallel A2A</div>
            <div class="timing-body">
              Financial + Market: max = 2,104ms<br/>
              Risk: 3,211ms<br/>
              <br/>
              <span class="timing-total" style="color:var(--success)">Total: ~5,315ms (1.35x faster)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="try-it">
        <div class="try-it-label">Run it yourself</div>
        <div class="try-it-body">
          pip install aiohttp openai<br/>
          git clone https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples<br/>
          cd examples/due-diligence<br/>
          python run.py Anthropic
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:16px;display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
          <a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/due-diligence" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size:0.85rem">View source</a>
          <a href="/a2a" class="btn-secondary" style="font-size:0.85rem">A2A protocol docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Wealth Management Case Study ── -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="case-hero">

      <div class="case-eyebrow">Case study</div>

      <h2 class="case-title">Wealth Management<br/>Multi-Agent Advisory</h2>

      <p class="case-lead">
        Four specialist AI agents — each with a different reasoning strategy — collaborate
        through a durable workflow to produce a comprehensive, compliance-checked investment
        recommendation. Human approval required before delivery.
      </p>

      <div class="metrics-row">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">4</div>
          <div class="metric-label">specialist agents</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">3</div>
          <div class="metric-label">reasoning strategies</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">6</div>
          <div class="metric-label">domain-specific tools</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">HITL</div>
          <div class="metric-label">human approval gate</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="subsection-title">Architecture</h3>

      <div class="arch-block">┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Workflow: <span style="color:var(--accent)">wealth_management_advisory</span>                    │
│                                                             │
│  AdvisoryState(client_id, risk, market, tax, recommendation)│
│                                                             │
│  Step 1: <span style="color:#c792ea">Risk Profiler</span>        strategy: plan-and-execute  │
│          └─ get_client_profile() → assess_risk_score()      │
│                                                             │
│  Step 2: <span style="color:#c792ea">Market Analyst</span>       strategy: react              │
│          └─ get_market_data() ×2 (broad → sector drill-in)  │
│                                                             │
│  Step 3: <span style="color:#c792ea">Tax Strategist</span>       strategy: plan-and-execute  │
│          └─ get_client_profile() → analyze_tax_implications()│
│                                                             │
│  Step 4: <span style="color:#c792ea">Portfolio Architect</span>   strategy: critic            │
│          └─ build_portfolio_allocation() →                   │
│             check_compliance()                              │
│          <span style="color:#c4956a">[HUMAN APPROVAL GATE]</span>                             │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘</div>

      <div class="case-body">
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why different strategies</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Risk Profiler → plan-and-execute:</strong> sequential, each step depends on the previous</li>
            <li><strong>Market Analyst → react:</strong> exploratory, iteratively drill into interesting sectors</li>
            <li><strong>Tax Strategist → plan-and-execute:</strong> systematic, must cover all applicable rules</li>
            <li><strong>Portfolio Architect → critic:</strong> draft-evaluate-refine for the most important deliverable</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why this matters for finance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Typed state</strong> — Pydantic models, not string-keyed dicts</li>
            <li><strong>Durable execution</strong> — survives crashes, resumes mid-workflow</li>
            <li><strong>Event sourcing</strong> — full audit trail for FINRA / Reg BI compliance</li>
            <li><strong>Human approval</strong> — licensed advisor sign-off before client delivery</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance checks</strong> — suitability, concentration limits, KYC/AML</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wm-comparison">
        <h3 class="subsection-title">JamJet vs Google ADK</h3>
        <div class="timing-grid">
          <div class="timing-card timing-fast">
            <div class="timing-label" style="color:var(--success)">JamJet</div>
            <div class="timing-body">
              3 reasoning strategies<br/>
              Typed Pydantic state<br/>
              human_approval=True<br/>
              Event-sourced audit trail<br/>
              <span class="timing-total" style="color:var(--success)">Compile to IR → durable runtime</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timing-card timing-slow">
            <div class="timing-label">Google ADK</div>
            <div class="timing-body">
              Model-determined reasoning<br/>
              Mutable dict state<br/>
              No approval primitive<br/>
              No audit trail<br/>
              <span class="timing-total" style="color:var(--error)">In-memory only (OSS)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="try-it">
        <div class="try-it-label">Try it</div>
        <div class="try-it-body">
          git clone https://github.com/jamjet-labs/jamjet<br/>
          cd examples/wealth-management-agents<br/>
          python jamjet_impl.py C-1001
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:16px;display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
          <a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/jamjet/tree/main/examples/wealth-management-agents" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size:0.85rem">View source</a>
          <a href="/blog/wealth-management-multi-agent/" class="btn-secondary" style="font-size:0.85rem">Read the deep dive</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Other Use Cases ── -->
<section style="background: var(--bg-alt);">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:48px">
      <span class="section-label">More use cases</span>
      <h2>Built for the hard problems</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin-top:12px;max-width:540px">Every pattern below maps to a JamJet primitive that handles it without custom infrastructure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="uc-grid">
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Customer Support Automation</h3>
        <p>Durable conversations that survive crashes. Human-in-the-loop escalation. MCP tools for CRM, Zendesk, Stripe.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Autonomous Code Review</h3>
        <p>Critic strategy with self-critique loop. Eval harness with LLM-judge scoring. Cost and iteration limits enforced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Research & Report Generation</h3>
        <p>Plan-and-execute over long-horizon tasks. Resumable mid-way. Per-step token cost via OTel traces.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Multi-Agent Data Pipelines</h3>
        <p>Parallel extractors via A2A. Typed state schemas. Agent Cards for dynamic discovery of new data sources.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Compliance & Risk Review</h3>
        <p>Human approval gates with durable state. Event sourcing for full audit trails. Policy engine with tool allowlists.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-card">
        <h3>Cross-Framework Agent Networks</h3>
        <p>A2A lets JamJet agents interoperate with LangChain, AutoGen, or any agent that speaks the protocol.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── CTA ── -->
<section>
  <div class="container" style="text-align:center;max-width:560px;">
    <h2>Start building</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);margin:16px 0 32px;">
      Run a working multi-agent example in under 5 minutes.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/jamjet/tree/main/examples/wealth-management-agents" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wealth management example</a>
      <a href="/quickstart" class="btn-secondary">Read the quickstart</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .uc-hero { padding: 80px 24px 48px; text-align: center; }
  .uc-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); margin-bottom: 16px; }

  .case-hero {
    background: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    border-radius: 12px; padding: 48px; max-width: 1060px; margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .case-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .case-title { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .case-lead { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 640px; }

  .metrics-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; margin: 32px 0; }
  .metric-card { background: var(--bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
  .metric-num { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: -0.04em; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .metric-label { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 4px; }

  .subsection-title {
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .arch-block {
    background: var(--bg-code); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 24px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5; color: #b0ac9f; white-space: pre; overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .case-body { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 40px; margin-top: 40px; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .case-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .body-block h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .body-block ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .body-block ul li {
    font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary); padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .body-block ul li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .a2a-endpoints { margin-top: 40px; }
  .endpoint-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
  .endpoint-card { background: var(--bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; }
  .endpoint-path { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .endpoint-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin: 0; line-height: 1.5; }

  .timing-comparison { margin-top: 40px; }
  .timing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .timing-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .timing-card { background: var(--bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 24px; }
  .timing-slow { opacity: 0.7; }
  .timing-label { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .timing-body { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 2; }
  .timing-total { font-weight: 700; }

  .try-it {
    margin-top: 40px; padding: 24px; background: var(--accent-bg);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139,115,85,0.2); border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .try-it-label { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .try-it-body { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 2; }

  .wm-comparison { margin-top: 40px; }

  .uc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; }
  .uc-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .uc-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .uc-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .uc-card p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
</style>
